50|$|There {{are many}} {{software}} applications that feature virtual cross-fades, for instance, burning-software for {{the recording of}} audio-CDs. Also many DAW’s (Pro Tools, Logic exc.) have this function. <b>Cross-fade</b> is normally found on samplers and usually based on velocity. The purpose of a <b>cross-fade</b> it to utilize a smooth changeover between two cut pieces of audio. Velocity cross-fading can be incorporated through a MIDI transformation device and where more than one note can be assigned to a given pad (note) on the MIDI keyboard; velocity cross-fading may be available.|$|E
